-- Transneft Retreats for Third Day as First-Quarter Profit Falls
-- B y   K s e n i a   G a l o u c h k o
-- 2012-06-21T13:25:20Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-06-21/transneft-retreats-for-third-day-as-first-quarter-profit-falls.html
OAO Transneft,  Russia ’s oil-pipeline
operator, fell for the third straight day as first-quarter
profit dropped 31 percent.  Transneft’s preferred shares retreated 1 percent to 45,236
rubles by 4:32 p.m. in Moscow, after declining as much as 2.1
percent earlier. Russia’s 30-stock Micex Index rose 0.3 percent
to 1,378.65.  First-quarter net income fell to 58.7 billion rubles, the
company said in a statement today.  -- Editors: Ash Kumar, Alex Nicholson  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
